@startuml fig-presentation-pipeline
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12

title Presentation layer pipeline (L6 functions)

rectangle "Application object\n(struct, dict, class)" as obj #FFE0B2
rectangle "Serialisation\n(JSON, XML, Protobuf)" as ser #FFF9C4
rectangle "Text encoding\n(UTF-8, ASCII)" as enc #BBDEFB
rectangle "Compression\n(gzip, brotli)" as cmp #E1BEE7
rectangle "Transport payload\n(bytes on the wire)" as wire #C8E6C9

obj -down-> ser : structure → format
ser -down-> enc : characters → bytes
enc -down-> cmp : reduce size
cmp -down-> wire : transmit

note right of ser
  Both endpoints must
  agree on the format.
end note

note right of enc
  Charset mismatch causes
  garbled text (mojibake).
end note

note right of cmp
  Trades CPU cycles
  for less bandwidth.
end note

legend bottom
  Each stage is a presentation-layer responsibility.
  The receiver applies the inverse pipeline: decompress → decode → deserialise.
  On the modern Internet these steps are handled by libraries, not a separate protocol.
endlegend
@enduml
